{"result": "AI technology and the peer review process are closely intertwined, with varying degrees of acceptance and regulation. While some guidelines permit the use of AI in specific aspects of the peer review process, such as identifying suitable reviewers or detecting duplicate submissions, others restrict its application due to concerns about bias, inaccuracies, and limitations in critical thinking and nuanced assessment. AI technology may be used in the final preparation of referee reports, provided that its use is explicitly disclosed. Additionally, peer reviewers may employ AI for language or word processing tasks, but they must declare such usage. Overall, the use of AI in the peer review process is subject to strict confidentiality and ethical guidelines, with a strong emphasis on transparency and non-compromise of the integrity of the review. However, there are clear restrictions on the use of AI technology, particularly in decision-making roles within the peer review process.", "input": "\nYou are an expert in academic publishing and AI policy analysis. You are skilled at interpreting complex regulatory frameworks and identifying key stakeholders and their interactions. You are adept at helping people map out the relationships and structural dynamics within academic publishing ecosystems and AI governance policies.\nUsing your expertise, you're asked to generate a comprehensive summary of the data provided below.\nGiven one or two entities, and a list of descriptions, all related to the same entity or group of entities.\nPlease concatenate all of these into a single, concise description in English. Make sure to include information collected from all the descriptions.\nIf the provided descriptions are contradictory, please resolve the contradictions and provide a single, coherent summary.\nMake sure it is written in third person, and include the entity names so we have the full context.\n\nEnrich it as much as you can with relevant information from the nearby text, this is very important.\n\nIf no answer is possible, or the description is empty, only convey information that is provided within the text.\n#######\n-Data-\nEntities: [\"AI TECHNOLOGY\", \"PEER REVIEW PROCESS\"]\nDescription List: [\"AI technologies may be used in the peer review process, but must not compromise confidentiality or integrity\", \"AI technology is not permitted to assist in the peer review process, as it may introduce bias or inaccuracies\", \"AI technology is not suitable for peer review due to its limitations in critical thinking and nuanced assessment\", \"AI technology may be used in the final preparation of referee reports but must be explicitly disclosed\", \"AI technology may be used in the peer review process, but its use must adhere to confidentiality and ethical guidelines\", \"AI technology may be used in the peer review process, but its use must be transparent\", \"AI technology may be used in the peer review process, but only in ways that do not compromise confidentiality or the integrity of the review\", \"AI technology supports the peer review process by identifying suitable reviewers and detecting duplicate submissions\", \"Peer reviewers may use AI technology to improve language or word processing, but must declare this\", \"The peer review process has restrictions on the use of AI technology, particularly in decision-making\"]\n#######\nOutput:", "parameters": {"model": "qwen-turbo", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": 0.0, "presence_penalty": 0.0, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 500, "n": 1}, "history": null}